urch of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":13,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":24,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":26,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":40,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":42,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705210,"age":55,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"John Peede was born in 1545, in Herefordshire, England. He married Elizabeth Howells in 1565. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 14 December 1608, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1545–14 December 1608":"1545–14. detsember 1608","1549–Female":"1549–Surnud","1566–Female":"1566–Surnud","1545–1608":"1545–1608","22 September 1566":"22. september 1566","1571":"1571","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1545":"1545","1600":"1600","1566":"1566","1565":"1565","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","14 December 1608":"14. detsember 1608","1608":"1608","1549":"1549","Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"1545–14 December 1608":"1545–14. joulukuuta 1608","1549–Female":"1549–Kuollut","1566–Female":"1566–Kuollut","1545–1608":"1545–1608","22 September 1566":"22. syyskuuta 1566","1571":"1571","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1545":"1545","1600":"1600","1566":"1566","1565":"1565","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","14 December 1608":"14. joulukuuta 1608","1608":"1608","1549":"1549","Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England"},"fr":{"1545–14 December 1608":"1545–14 décembre 1608","1549–Female":"1549–Décédée","1566–Female":"1566–Décédée","1545–1608":"1545–